OL,4,Crestoration of memorial
OL,6,FToday, it is understood that many of
OL,7,Fthem were suffering from Post
OL,8,FTraumatic Stress Disorder - a
OL,9,Fcondition that was not recognised as a
OL,10,Fmedical condition until 1980.
OL,12,FIn 2006, 90 years after their deaths,
OL,13,Fthe soldiers were officially pardoned
OL,14,Fby the British Government.
OL,16,FThe memorial has suffered repeated
OL,17,Fdamage over the years due to flooding
OL,18,Ffrom the adjacent River Tame.
